comment.narrative:
- HRCSL has not published an annual report or updated their website;
- No/limited systematic inspection of prisons and police stations;
- Majority of people in prison have not been legally represented [no data available];
- Weak data generation & management  mechanisms  and weak advocacy forums on human rights issues (Human Rights 
  WG has not met for over 2 years);
- Limited public legal information and awareness campaign;
- Limited knowledge of HRCSL staff on new emerging human rights issues;
- Limited institutional capacity of HRCSL and perception of non-effectiveness and independence among public;
- Matrix of Universal Peer Review (UPR) recommendations developed by Commission in 2014 and in place but with no other 
  treaty body mechanisms;                                                                                              
- No basic information published on key human rights rights instruments including on women's rights; and
- Members of public often come to the Commission for complaints not relevant to their mandate.
